'''Sir Mac'''<ref name="crc">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/bts/article/f20030502/index.html|text=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases|int=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases}}</ref> was a [[Bith/Legends|Bith]] refugee.<ref name="ImageAttack">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/explore/attack/2003/04/imageattack20030403.html|series=Image Attack|text=Rough and Tumble Lot}}</ref> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], they visited the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] and the the streets of the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] on Coruscant when [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] were pursuing the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]. He witnessed Anakin's fall from Zam's [[Koro-2 all-environment exodrive airspeeder|Koro-2 all-environment exodrive]] [[Airspeeder/Legends|airspeeder]] and watched as he regained himself and continued pursuing Zam. While so, the Bith stroked his chin, most likely a gesture of confusion. While in the Outlander Club and on the streets of Coruscant, the Bith wore a cheap suit of a greenish tint. The Bith was also one of many Coruscant Citizens that were impoverished.<ref name="Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

